018-09-20|publisher=Nogizaka46LLC|language=ja}}</ref>||Held graduation concert on February 24, 2019\n|-\n|{{nihongo|[[Misa Et\u014d]]|\u885b\u85e4\u7f8e\u5f69}}||{{Birth date and age|1993|1|4}}||[[\u014cita Prefecture|\u014cita]]||1||March 31, 2019||\n|-\n||{{nihongo|Karin It\u014d|\u4f0a\u85e4\u304b\u308a\u3093}}||{{Birth date and age|1993|5|26}}||Kanagawa||2||May 24, 2019<ref name=nikkankaringrad>{{cite news|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/entertainment/news/201905250000029.html|language=ja|title=\u4e43\u6728\u5742\u5352\u696d\u306e\u4f0a\u85e4\u304b\u308a\u3093\u300c\u8a87\u308a\u306b\u601d\u3046\u300d\u30b9\u30d4\u30fc\u30c1\u5168\u6587|work=Nikkan Sports|date=2019-05-25|access-date=2019-07-29}}</ref>||\n|-\n|{{nihongo|Y\u016bri Sait\u014d|\u6589\u85e4\u512a\u91cc}}||{{Birth date and age|1993|7|20}}||Tokyo||1||June 30, 2019<ref name=nikkanyuurigrad>{{cite news|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/entertainment/news/201906300000692.html|language=ja|title=\u5143\u4e43\u6728\u5742\u6589\u85e4\u512a\u91cc\u30b3\u30e1\u30c7\u30a3\u30fc\u821e\u53f0\u51fa\u6f14\u3001\u5352\u696d\u5f8c\u521d\u4ed5\u4e8b|work=Nikkan Sports|date=2019-07-01|access-date=2019-07-29}}</ref>||\n|-\n|{{nihongo|[[Reika Sakurai]]|\u685c\u4e95\u73b2\u9999}}||{{Birth date and age|1994|5|16}}||Kanagawa||1||September 1, 2019||Former captain\n|-\n|{{nihongo|Kotoko Sasaki|\u4f50\u3005\u6728\u7434\u5b50}}||{{Birth date and age|1998|8|28}}||Saitama||2||March 31, 2020||\n|}\n\n==Discography==\n{{Main|Nogizaka46 discography}}\nNogizaka46 has released twenty-five singles and five albums, as well as numerous music videos and concert performance videos. Million-selling singles have included \"[[Influencer (song)|Influencer]]\" and \"[[Synchronicity (song)|Synchronicity]]\", each of which won a [[Japan Record Awards]] Grand Prix, as well as \"[[Kaerimichi wa T\u014dmawari Shitaku Naru]]\" and \"[[Sing Out! (song)|Sing Out!]]\". Album releases include the studio albums ''[[T\u014dmei na Iro]]'', ''[[Sorezore no Isu]]'', ''[[Umaretekara Hajimete Mita Yume]]'', and ''[[Ima ga Omoide ni Naru made]]''. The group also released a compilation of \"under\" songs, written for members who perform at concerts but are not part of the main selection group for promoting singles, with the title ''[[Boku dake no Kimi: Under Super Best]]''.\n\n== Tours and concerts ==\nSince their first \"Birthday Live\" concert in 2013, Nogizaka46 has held annual concerts during which the group performs all or most of the songs in their catalogue. At the first Birthday Live concert at [[Makuhari Messe]], the group performed all of the songs from their first four singles to an audience of 9,000 people.<ref name=1stbirthdaylive>{{cite news|lang=ja|url=https://natalie.mu/music/news/85424|title=\u4e43\u6728\u574246\u3001\u30c7\u30d3\u30e5\u30fc1\u5468\u5e74\u3067\u5168\u66f2\u30e9\u30a4\u30d6\uff06\u65b0\u66f2\u3082\u521d\u62ab\u9732|work=[[Natalie (website)|Natalie]]|date=2013-02-23|access-date=2020-02-10}}</ref> In 2014 they performed for 13,000 fans at [[Yokohama Arena]],<ref name=2ndbirthdaylive>{{cite news|lang=ja|url=https://natalie.mu/music/news/110449|title=\u30b5\u30d7\u30e9\u30a4\u30ba\u9023\u767a\uff01\u4e43\u6728\u574246\u30c7\u30d3\u30e5\u30fc2\u5468\u5e74\u795d\u30465\u6642\u9593\u30e9\u30a4\u30d6|work=[[Natalie (website)|Natalie]]|date=2014-02-23|access-date=2020-02-10}}</ref> and the following year they performed 69 songs in a seven-and-a-half hour birthday concert for 38,000 fans at [[Seibu Dome]].<ref name=3rdbirthdaylive>{{cite news|lang=ja|url=https://mdpr.jp/music/detail/1469434|title=\u4e43\u6728\u574246\u897f\u91ce\u4e03\u702c\u3089\u611f\u6d99 AKB48\u5c0f\u5d8b\u967d\u83dc\u3082\u30b5\u30d7\u30e9\u30a4\u30ba\u767b\u5834 7\u6642\u9593\u534a\u30fb\u516869\u66f2\u306b3\u4e078000\u4eba\u71b1\u72c2\uff1c3\u5468\u5e74\u30e9\u30a4\u30d6\uff0f\u5199\u771f\u7279\u96c6\uff1e|work=Modelpress|date=2015-02-22|access-date=2020-02-10}}</ref> The group's growing catalogue and fan base led to longer concerts at larger venues, including three-day concerts at [[Meiji Jingu Stadium]] in 2016<ref name=4thbirthdaylive>{{cite news|lang=ja|url=https://natalie.mu/music/news/199796|title=\u4e43\u6728\u574246\u3001\u660e\u6cbb\u795e\u5bae\u7403\u5834\u516c\u6f143DAYS\u958b\u5e55\uff01\u685c\u4e95\u73b2\u9999\u3082\u5fa9\u5e30|work=[[Natalie (website)|Natalie]]|date=2016-08-29|access-date=2020-02-10}}</ref> and  [[Saitama Super Arena]] in 2017,<ref name=5thbirthdaylive>{{cite news|lang=ja|url=https://natalie.mu/music/news/221529|title=\u300c\u81ea\u5206\u3067\u9078\u3093\u3060\u9053\u306e\u5148\u306b\u6b63\u89e3\u304c\u3042\u308b\u3068\u4fe1\u3058\u3066\u307e\u3059\u300d\u4e43\u6728\u574246\u6a4b\u672c\u5948\u3005\u672a\u3001\u6d99\u306e\u5352\u696d\u30e9\u30a4\u30d6|work=[[Natalie (website)|Natalie]]|date=2017-02-21|access-date=2020-02-10}}</ref> and a four-day Birthday Live concert in 2019 at [[Kyocera Dome]], at which the group performed all 177 songs in their catalogue.<ref name=7thbirthdaylive>{{cite news|lang=ja|url=https://natalie.mu/music/news/321324|title=\u4e43\u6728\u574246\u897f\u91ce\u4e03\u702c\u304c\u5730\u5143\u5927\u962a\u3067\u30e9\u30b9\u30c8\u30b9\u30c6\u30fc\u30b8\u30017\u5e74\u9593\u306e\u30a2\u30a4\u30c9\u30eb\u4eba\u751f\u306b\u611f\u8b1d|work=[[Natalie (website)|Natalie]]|date=2019-02-15|access-date=2020-02-10}}</ref> \n\nNogizaka46 has also held a national summer concert tour each year at venues across Japan, concluding with a show in [[Tokyo]]. In 2013, the tour included ten performances in five cities, with a final three-hour concert at [[Yoyogi National Gymnasium]].<ref name=1stsummertour>{{cite news|lang=ja|url=https://natalie.mu/music/news/100850|title=\u4e43\u6728\u574246\u3001\u5727\u5dfb\u306e\u4ee3\u3005\u6728\u7af6\u6280\u5834\u30e9\u30a4\u30d6\u306b\u8a082\u4e074000\u4eba\u52d5\u54e1|work=[[Natalie (website)|Natalie]]|date=2013-10-07|access-date=2020-02-10}}</ref> Four years later, the national tour concluded with a two-day performance for 100,000 fans at [[Tokyo Dome]].<ref name=5thsummertour>{{cite news|lang=ja|url=https://natalie.mu/music/news/255978|title=\u4e0a\u308a\u7d9a\u3051\u308b\u4e43\u6728\u574246\u3001\u521d\u6771\u4eac\u30c9\u30fc\u30e0\u3067\u898b\u636e\u3048\u305f\u3055\u3089\u306a\u308b\u9ad8\u307f\u300c\u3082\u3063\u3068\u3059\u3054\u3044\u6240\u3078\u300d|work=[[Natalie (website)|Natalie]]|date=2017-11-09|access-date=2020-02-10}}</ref> In addition to the regular summer concert tour, the group has occasionally held concerts to commemorate holidays such as [[Christmas]],<ref name=1stxmas>{{cite news|lang=ja|url=https://natalie.mu/music/news/106234|title=\u4e43\u6728\u574246\u3001\u521d\u6b66\u9053\u9928\u3067\u30d5\u30a1\u30f31\u4e072000\u4eba\u3068Xmas\u30d1\u30fc\u30c6\u30a3|date=2013-10-20|access-date=2020-02-10}}</ref> or to highlight members of the group who have not been chosen to perform on the main singles.<ref name=underlive2018>{{cite news|lang=ja|url=https://natalie.mu/music/news/313126|title=\u4e43\u6728\u574246\u30a2\u30f3\u30c0\u30fc\u30e9\u30a4\u30d6\u3067\u5ddd\u5f8c\u967d\u83dc\u304c\u6d99\u306e\u5352\u696d\u300c7\u5e74\u9593\u3067\u672c\u5f53\u306b\u5927\u5207\u306a\u3082\u306e\u304c\u3067\u304d\u305f\u300d|work=[[Natalie (website)|Natalie]]|date=2018-12-21|access-date=2020-02-10}}</ref>\n\n== Filmography ==\n\n=== Documentary film ===\n* ''Kanashimi no Wasurekata : Documentary of Nogizaka46'' (2015)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.allcinema.net/prog/show_c.php?num_c=352056|script-title=ja:\u6620\u753b \u60b2\u3057\u307f\u306e\u5fd8\u308c\u65b9 DOCUMENTARY of \u4e43\u6728\u574246|accessdate=2017-01-29|publisher=Stingray|work=allcinema|language=ja}}</ref>\n* ''Itsunomanika, Kokoniiru: Documentary of Nogizaka46'' (2019)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.allcinema.net/cinema/368732|script-title=ja:\u3044\u3064\u306e\u307e\u306b\u304b\u3001\u3053\u3053\u306b\u3044\u308b Documentary of \u4e43\u6728\u574246|accessdate=2020-01-13|publisher=Stingray|work=allcinema|language=ja}}<