mitchell98computing.html}}\n*{{cite web |last=Simon |first=Daniel R. |year = 1994 |title = On the Power of Quantum Computation |publisher = Institute of Electrical and Electronic Engineers Computer Society Press |url = http://citeseer.ist.psu.edu/simon94power.html}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Commons|Quantum computer}}\n* [[Stanford Encyclopedia of Philosophy]]: \"[http://plato.stanford.edu/entries/qt-quantcomp/ Quantum Computing]\" by Amit Hagar and Michael E. Cuffaro.\n* {{springer|title=Quantum computation, theory of|id=p/q130020}}\n* [https://quantum.country/qcvc Quantum computing for the very curious] by Andy Matuschak and [[Michael Nielsen]]\n \n;Lectures\n* [https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PL1826E60FD05B44E4 Quantum computing for the determined] \u2013 22 video lectures by [[Michael Nielsen]]\n* [http://www.quiprocone.org/Protected/DD_lectures.htm Video Lectures] by [[David Deutsch]]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20160303183533/http://www.quantware.ups-tlse.fr/IHP2006/ Lectures at the Institut Henri Poincar\u00e9 (slides and videos)]\n* [http://nanohub.org/resources/4778 Online lecture on An Introduction to Quantum Computing, Edward Gerjuoy (2008)]\n* Lomonaco, Sam. [http://www.csee.umbc.edu/~lomonaco/Lectures.html#OxfordLectures Four Lectures on Quantum Computing given at Oxford University in July 2006]\n\n{{Quantum computing}}\n{{emerging technologies|quantum=yes|other=yes}}\n{{Computer science}}\n{{Quantum mechanics topics}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Quantum information science| ]]\n[[Category:Quantum computing| ]]\n[[Category:Models of computation]]\n[[Category:Quantum cryptography]]\n[[Category:Information theory]]\n[[Category:Computational complexity theory]]\n[[Category:Classes of computers]]\n[[Category:Theoretical computer science]]\n[[Category:Open problems]]\n[[Category:Computer-related introductions in 1980]]\n[[Category:Emerging technologies]]\n", "name_user": "Jaydavidmartin", "label": "safe", "comment": "fixed spacing and s